  "baseRefName": "main",
  "body": "## Summary\n\nAn externally-generated **Dealix Launch Package (V1 + V2)** was uploaded with instructions to `cp -R` it over the repo. Reviewed against the actual codebase, that path would have been **destructive**, so this PR does a **safe selective integration** instead (option chosen by the founder).\n\nThe package re-implements ~90% of what the repo already has — in less mature, ungoverned form — and a few of its instructions directly conflict with the repo doctrine (`Govern before automating` / no external auto-send / no scraping).\n\n## What this PR does\n\n**1. Archives the full package verbatim** under `docs/external/launch_package_v2/` as inert reference:\n- `.tsx` files sit outside `frontend/` → Next.js never builds them.\n- `.github/workflows/*.yml` sit outside root `.github/` → GitHub never runs them.\n\n**2. Promotes only net-new, doctrine-compliant pieces**, adapted to repo conventions:\n- `docs/compliance/OUTBOUND_AND_DATA_POLICY_AR.md` — `docs/compliance/` had no outbound policy; linked to the Operating Doctrine + PDPL guide.\n- `scripts/launch_package/` — approval-first, stdlib-only prospecting helpers (lead scoring → daily command center → outreach **draft** queue). They **never send**, **never scrape**, emit `needs_founder_review`, and ship a sample seed + reconciled 9-column schema. Verified to run end-to-end.\n\n**3. Skips** (archive-only, with reasons documented):\n- Duplicates: 80+ `landing/` pages, bilingual `[locale]/{pricing,privacy,services}` pages, war room, CRM, offers.\n- Destructive: `dealix-launch-readiness.yml` (runs data-mutating scripts on **every PR/push**); frontend page overwrites that would inject a **3rd conflicting pricing model**.\n\n**4. Adds `docs/external/LAUNCH_PACKAGE_RECONCILIATION_AR.md`** — a file-by-file map (promoted / already-exists / skipped-with-reason) plus a pricing-conflict callout and recommended next steps using the repo's existing tooling.\n\n## Safety\n\n- **Purely additive** — 51 files added, **0 modified**. No existing file overwritten.\n- No frontend/CI/pricing wiring touched. No customer data committed (sample seed is placeholder; real data stays in gitignored `data/prospects/`).\n\n## Open follow-ups (not in this PR)\n\n- Unify pricing on a single source (`docs/pricing.md` + `PricingPlans`) before any public site update.\n- If `/industries` or `/contact` routes are wanted, build them to repo conventions (`AppLayout` + bilingual + `generateMetadata` + async `params`) — not the package stubs.\n\nhttps://claude.ai/code/session_01EGDnXR95LP8JgxasFmboJy\n\n---\n_Generated by [Claude Code](https://claude.ai/code/session_01EGDnXR95LP8JgxasFmboJy)_",
